Read and Merge 538 Data

pols <- read_csv("./fivethirtyeight_datasets/pols-month.csv") %>% 
  clean_names() %>% 
  mutate(president = ifelse(prez_gop == 0, "dem", "gop")) %>% 
  mutate(date = lubridate::floor_date(mon,"month")) %>% 
  select(-mon) %>% 
  arrange(date)
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   mon = col_date(format = ""),
##   prez_gop = col_integer(),
##   gov_gop = col_integer(),
##   sen_gop = col_integer(),
##   rep_gop = col_integer(),
##   prez_dem = col_integer(),
##   gov_dem = col_integer(),
##   sen_dem = col_integer(),
##   rep_dem = col_integer()
## )
gdp <- read_csv("./fivethirtyeight_datasets/GDP.csv", na = ".") %>% 
  clean_names() %>% 
  select(date, gdp_value = value) %>% 
  mutate(date = lubridate::floor_date(date,"month"))
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   DATE = col_date(format = ""),
##   VALUE = col_double()
## )
five38 <- inner_join(pols, gdp, by = "date") %>% 
  select(date, everything())

GDP Value over Time

five38 %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = date, y = gdp_value, color = president)) + geom_point() +   
  geom_smooth(alpha = 0.1) + labs(x = "Date", y = "GDP Value", title = "GDP Value Over Time for Each Presidential Party")
